- cs.DB (Databases): The paper describes the use of an Oracle backend and Google Cloud SQL-MySQL for data storage and management.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper mentions the use of SSL-enabled web browsers for accessing the prototype, indicating a focus on security.
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science): The paper does not fit neatly into any specific sub-category, but could potentially fall under this catch-all category.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The use of a cloud computing platform for multi-center trials involves distributed computing and could potentially fall under this sub-category.
